metadata.name: Moonlit Mountains #90
metadata.description:
In this work I tried to depict variations of a forested mountain landscape lit by moonlight. The trees, mountains, sky, clouds, moon, stars, everything is generated 100% with code using random numbers from various distributions.

There are many features that are randomly chosen and used to guide the composition. The values for each feature are not equally probable. Some rare features are a Blue Moon (5%) and Shooting Star (15%).

Features:

Steepness: 1 -> 10 (larger values are steeper)

Big Trees: 0 -> 3  (large trees in foreground)

Tree Density: Low, Medium, High

Moon Phase: New, Waning Crescent, Waning Quarter, Full, Waxing Quarter, Waxing Crescent

Moon Size: Small, Medium, Large, Very Large

Fog Level: Low, Medium, High, Very High

Cloud Level: None, Low, Medium, High, Very High

Stars: None, Low, Medium, High, Very High

Prevailing Winds: Leftward, Neutral, Rightward

Moon Color: Blue, Red, Orange, Yellow, Silver

Shooting Star: true, false

Sky Color: many

metadata.name: MONOLITH #233
metadata.description:
Very limited facts are known about these strange monolithic structures. Black, rectilinear, similar to obsidian stone but made of strange materials. According to legend, an ancient civilization of high intelligence, called the Explorers of Latent Space, distributed hundreds of monoliths throughout time and space in order to study the behavior of species in the infinite Universe.

Some say that it is the divine intelligence of God. Others say that, in spite of their objectual and material condition, the monoliths possess their own consciousness and an intelligence beyond the natural and artificial. Their purpose or objective, to this day, remains a mystery.

_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_

this work is done only with code, using threejs and p5js

metadata.name: Southern Gothic #31
metadata.description:
â€œSouthern Gothicâ€ is my debut release on the fxhash platform. The project is created entirely through code. All copyrights are released to the holder of each image output, even for commercial purposes.

â€œSouthern Gothicâ€ borrows its name from the literary genre made famous by writers like Flannery Oâ€™Connor and Carson McCullers. Rather than illustrating a singular setting, the code generates an entire rural townscape, thereby, blurring the boundaries between representation and narrative. The individual scenes are framed frontally with an intentionally flat aesthetic character, referencing traditional folk art of the American South. The absence of human figures within these scenes adds to their overwhelming sense of darkness and forlorn. Observing multiple scenes side-by-side, one may even get the strange feeling that something terrible has happened (or is about to happen) in this rural landscape.

Pressing the down arrow saves the coded output as a .png image.

metadata.name: A24Z #700
metadata.description:
Every artist and collector feels the joy of both creating and collecting. But if I could share the joy of creating with collectors. And collectors with their family and friends, what may be an additive process of joy is now perhaps exponential. Joy to the power of 26 to be exact. 

In this work I invite my friends and collectors to collaborate with me. Though not in coding, but together in a process of creating narratives and visuals. Code and story. We didnâ€™t use github, just a simple p5.js editor to try out different programs and palettes. Pedrofe and J0rdan pick their palettes tastefully and carefully. okeoke, perhaps more of a genius than he lets on, picks his palettes blind. No hex color picker. Just straight up rhymes.  

In our discussions verbal language was forbidden. Only emojis were allowed to express our tastes and views. Each emojis put down on google doc was taken with absolutely seriousness. 

Pedro: Loves to taking his daily walks on â€œMagic Mushroom Mountainâ€

J0rdan: Wonders about â€œQuark Question Quichesâ€

Okeoke: Just get lost in â€œFinnegansâ€™ Flower Fields.â€

It has been a great joy to present our illustration book A24Z, 8 more than you know who. Each page expresses the alphabet with the best of our knowledge in semantics and sarcasm. Collect just 1 page, collect the alphabets that spell out your name, collect the whole A to Z. Read it to your children or loved ones. Though you might need to interpolate or extrapolate with great imagination which children all have. But most importantly, like all children, have fun!

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed or broken, test capture at 300 sec.

metadata.name: CrossWorlds #88
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180Â°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.
